        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 3 at 5:33PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 533 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Miller, or 10 miles south of Linden, moving southeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sweet Water, Wayne, Surginer, Miller, Magnolia, Vineland, and
Octagon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
